"This mini blogging platform is developed as part of an internship opportunity provided by Unified Mentor, showcasing real-world skills in full-stack development using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Node.js. The application is seamlessly integrated with Firebase for dynamic and reliable data storage."

Learning Outcome & Impact
This project goes beyond a typical frontend buildâ€”it combines frontend finesse with backend functionality using Node.js, and leverages Firebase as a scalable cloud-based database. It demonstrates the power of using core web technologies to create real-world, production-ready applications, even without complex frameworks.


Getting Started
First, run the development server:

npm run dev
# or
yarn dev


Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) 
with your browser to see the result.
